    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Waiting for the Plane</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ruth F Block letter says one result of interminable delays at airports (July 16 article) is the misbehavior of the children forced to endure them</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Despite Efforts, Airport Delays Are Worsening'' (front page, July 16) doesn't discuss how one segment of those who experience the increasingly long and interminable delays at airports -- young travelers and their families -- react to those delays.</p>
        <p>Whether children are traveling with family members or are flying alone to visit a divorced parent, a grandparent or another family member, it is likely that they will start acting up or misbehave in one way or another.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Despite Efforts, Airport Delays Are Worsening'' (front page, July 16) doesn't discuss how one segment of those who experience the increasingly long and interminable delays at airports -- young travelers and their families -- react to those delays.</p>
        <p>Whether children are traveling with family members or are flying alone to visit a divorced parent, a grandparent or another family member, it is likely that they will start acting up or misbehave in one way or another.</p>
        <p>It would be unrealistic for parents to expect their children not to be rude, whine, complain or resort to other forms of bad behavior in such circumstances.</p>
        <p>RUTH F. BLOCK  New York, July 20, 2000</p>
      </block>
